\n\r\nparser = argparse.ArgumentParser()\r\nparser.add_argument('--s3-bucket', type=str, help='check authentication repo for bucket names')\r\nparser.add_argument('--input-path', type=validate_filepath_arg)\r\nparser.add_argument('--output-path', type=validate_filepath_arg)\r\nargs = parser.parse_args(['download', '--s3-bucket', 'default', '--input-path', '/path/to/somewhere.txt', '--output-path', '/path/to/somewhere.txt'])\r\n```\r\n\r\n> \r\n> >>python3 example_bug.py \r\n> usage: example_bug.py [-h] [--s3-bucket S3_BUCKET] [--input-path INPUT_PATH]\r\n>                       [--output-path OUTPUT_PATH]\r\n> example_bug.py: error: argument --input-path: reason=MALFORMED_ABS_PATH, target-platform=universal, description=an invalid absolute file path (/path/to/somewhere.txt) for the platform (universal). specify an appropriate platform or 'auto'.\r\n\r\nThe error is raised in: \r\n`    def validate_abspath(self, value: PathType) -> None:`\r\n...\r\n``` \r\n       if self._is_universal() and any([is_posix_abs, is_nt_abs]):\r\n           raise err_object\r\n```", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/thombashi/pathvalidate/issues/10", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/thombashi/pathvalidate", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/thombashi/pathvalidate/issues/10/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/thombashi/pathvalidate/issues/10/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/thombashi/pathvalidate/issues/10/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/thombashi/pathvalidate/issues/10", "id": 463185101, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NjMxODUxMDE=", "number": 10, "title": "validate len of every windows path part", "user": {"login": "UncleGoogle", "id": 12197825, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyMTk3ODI1", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/12197825?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/UncleGoogle", "html_url": "https://github.com/UncleGoogle",